<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,980,1005]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species could be distinguished from its congeners by: 1) body entirely dark brown; 2) temple not dilated, and subparallel; 3) head punctation; 4) scape of antennae quite long; 5) internal sac morphology.
</paragraph>
